page_summary: This page consists primarily of glossary definitions and acronyms relevant to breast cancer clinical research, including terms related to disease characterization, imaging, organizations, and standard data structures. It mentions key efficacy endpoints such as Overall Survival (OS), Progression-Free Survival (PFS), Pathologic Complete Response (pCR), and Relapse-Free Survival (RFS), but provides only their abbreviations and not detailed definitions or measurement criteria.
